column5: Tried between Mohawk Island. and shore, nothing this time. Went strait out to deeper water, marked lots of fish near bottom in 65' all we could catch was Sheephead. Heard Steve(Fishmaster) on the radio catching. So we trolled west to 80'. By the time we got there Steve  was leaving with all the fish    He said they shut down. So we trolled the area till 6:00pm and left. We did manage 1 Walleye and a surprise, a nice Coho. The Coho hit a worm Harness on a Deep Driver, back 150', 2 1/2 setting, Speed 2.0.
Nice Fish ...   next time pull gear and run ...see ya out there
That's a solid looking Coho Dave. When will it be coming out of the smoker.
Winds were INSANE out in MAITLAND.... Was at the Pier on Sunday... Couldn't fish for more than 1hr cause of winds!
